# S03 — ARCHITECT Brief: eWeLink Refinement

role: ARCHITECT
sprint: S03
objective: Design patterns that scale to Tuya in S04

design-focus:
  - Abstraction: Device provider interface (eWeLink today, Tuya tomorrow)
  - Data flow: Server → Socket.IO → Vue components
  - Shared models: Device, Status, PowerReading (reusable)

patterns:
  - Adapter/Strategy for cloud providers (eWeLink, Tuya)
  - Single source of truth for device state (server)
  - Card component composition (slot/props for device-type variants)

layer-boundaries:
  - Backend: eWeLink client service, device normalization
  - Frontend: Dashboard layout, DeviceCard, Chart wrappers
  - No direct eWeLink SDK in client; all via API/socket

decisions-to-document:
  - Device schema (id, type, channels, lastSeen, power, etc.)
  - API shape for device list and control
  - Socket event naming convention
